  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "clear",
    "intended": "A unitary divisor of $n$ is $d\\mid n$ such that $(d,n/d)=1$. A number $n\\geq 1$ is a unitary perfect number if it is the sum of its unitary divisors (aside from $n$ itself).\n\nAre there only finite many unitary perfect numbers?",
